<br>
 What happens, is that EQ is like a lot of technology, you have early adapters, people who put up with the bugs and bullshit til they get the hang of it. That is why people were willing to grind through exp penalties, underpowered classes and waiting lists in sol B. How many people that have started playing in the last year, would be willing to wait 4 or more hours to get in a window room group ? Think about it, when was the last time you heard anyone complain about how hard it is to get a group somewhere ? Doesn't matter, now, any class can solo if need be ( thanks DaoC for that idea ). Verant figures ( and probably correctly ) that the hard core players have already been playing for 2 +  years. Now they must attract the more casual gamers, people who want to log on an hour or so, accomplish something , and log off ( and there is nothing wrong with that I might add ).<br>
<br>
  I will agree, EQ is heads and shoulders above any game in the genre, and it will be a while before anything comes close to it. Verant got it right the first time , though I still say they have no idea why their game was popular, with all the problems EQ has had over the years, it was able to keep growing, pretty amazing when you think about it.<br>
<br>
  Personally I hope EQ is able to get 1 million   customers paying 20 bucks a month, before it finally dies out. That way, it will encourage other companies to invest in online gaming and we will finally see something superior to Everquest. Till that day though, EQ is as good as it gets. <br>
<br>
  One thing that I think Verant hasn't figured out, it is a lot of the things that people hated so much about EQ, is exactly what made EQ so attractive. The Exp penalties, the Hell levels, the long boring camps, the rare drop loot, Exp losses the quests that took forever . These things , though counterintuitive , in hindsight provided the best memories in EQ. And that is what separated EQ from the rest of the pack. When you finally got something, it meant something because of all the stupid bullshit you had to put up with to get it. <br>
<br>
